Desiccant-based ventilation system
Manufacturerâ€™s information: SEMCO Revolution Unit REV 2250, SEMCO enthalpy recovery module FRV 2000

Installation date: TBD

System Description:

The SEMCO ventilation system integrates a 3000 cfm circulation fan, a 50 kW air-based heat pump for cooling/heating, and an active solid desiccant wheel, which can be used for air dehumidification in summer and air heating in winter.








There are overall 8 steps to precise comfort under DOAS mode During the summer time, the processed air from energy recovery wheel is drawn through the direct expansion (DX) cooling coil (position 3), the air is cooled and dehumidified he re. The cool, saturated air is then split into two portions: one portion passes through the active desiccant wheel as indicated in position 4, where the air is further dehumidified to a very low dew point; another portion bypasses around the wheel through a modulating damper controlled by the DDC system as indication in position 5. The warm dry air from the wheel is then mixed with the cool, saturated air (position 6) to provide supply air at the set humidity and temperature condition in IW. During the winter time, the refrigeration system is operated at its reversed mode, and the gas burner at the regeneration side of the ventilation unit (position 7) is operated to provide addition heat to the supply air. Due to the high local gas price, the operation cost is fairly high. Attempts had been made to utilize the waste heat from CHP (combined heat and power) to generate heat energy; however the CHP failed to provide expected effect. Therefore gas burner was still in use
